# Committed on purpose (ADR 018 pattern — like DATABASE_CA_CERT): these three
# values are PUBLIC BY DESIGN (they ship in every browser bundle; the
# publishable key is Supabase's rate-limited/RLS-scoped client key, docs/
# RUNBOOK.md). They must be present at BUILD time in CI, and the Vercel
# project cannot provide them there: the team's sensitive-env-vars policy
# forces every Vercel env var to write-only, which `vercel pull` receives as
# EMPTY values — that is what broke production on 2026-07-04 (Internal Server
# Error on every route: the middleware was compiled with empty strings; see
# lessons-learned). Real secrets (DATABASE_URL, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
# STRIPE_*) stay in the Vercel env store — they are runtime-injected and
# sensitive works fine for them. NEVER put a secret in this file.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://vqvohfqapjfdpbojtezx.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_6KuLq2BgUm68Q8kRUTlM-g_u1xl3tZ_
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://checkdecijfers.vercel.app
